		<h4>St George’s Church</h4>
		<p><em>St George’s Church, Orleton, has been a place of worship since the 12th century and was built from local sandstone. 
			Additions and alterations were made over the next two centuries. 
			It has some remarkable features including a highly decorated twelfth century font, Jacobean pulpit, 
			14th century churchyard cross and identifiable sculptured heads over the chancel arch. 
			A detailed plan of the churchyard is available in the church porch.</em></p>
		<p><em>St George’s church services follow a regular pattern. You will find a warm welcome on a Sunday morning.</em></p>

		<p><em>For more information please see the 
			<a href="https://stgeorgesorleton.org.uk" target="_blank">St George's website</a>.</em></p>

